e for an exomoon\ncandidate Kepler-1625b I, which we briefly describe ahead of scheduled\nobservations of the target with the Hubble Space Telescope.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 26 Jul 2017 17:58:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 18 Oct 2017 20:07:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-27"}
